Although no excavation has been conducted, surveys indicate that the surrounding trench has a width of 5–9 meters. A surrounding embankment follows the outer edge of the trench, giving the mound a total length of approximately 85 meters, including the embankment. The lack of {{ill|haniwa|ja|埴輪|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and the mound's construction in the {{ill|7th century|ja|7世紀|qq=draft|qq=draft}} have been noted. However, the difference in type compared to the nearby {{ill|Danotsuka Kofun|ja|段ノ塚古墳|1=Dannozuka Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft}} along the Sakutagawa River, which was also built in the 7th century as a square Kofun, remains a topic for further study.

