'''Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun''' (山室姫塚古墳) is a [[:en:Kofun|Kofun]] located in [[:en:Sanmu|Sanmu]], [[:en:Chiba Prefecture|Chiba Prefecture]], in the Matsuo-machi Yamamuro area. It has been Historic Site1 as a historical site by Chiba Prefecture<ref name=Chiba>{{Cite web|Japanese|author=Chiba Prefecture Education Promotion Division, Historic Site Section, Designated Historic Site Team|url=https://www.pref.chiba.lg.jp/kyouiku/bunkazai/bunkazai/p411-078.html|title=Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun|work=Chiba Prefecture|accessdate=2020-05-18}}</ref>.

== Overview ==
The Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun is situated on a plateau 33 meters above sea level on the western bank of the middle reaches of the {{ill|Kidogawa River|ja|木戸川 (千葉県)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kidogawa River|qq=}}, which flows through the center of the {{ill|Kujukuri Plain|ja|九十九里平野|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kujukuri Plain|qq=}}. It is part of the Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster, which consists of 16 Kofuns. Positioned at the tip of the plateau, the Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun is the first mound in the cluster and measures 64–66 meters in diameter and 9 meters in height, making it the largest {{ill|round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/round Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=}} in Chiba Prefecture. 

In contrast to nearby kofun clusters, such as the {{ill|Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|小池大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}} and the [[:en:Shibayama Kofun Cluster|Shibayama Kofun Cluster]] upstream on the eastern bank, or the {{ill|Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|ja|大堤権現塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kabuki Kofun Cluster|ja|蕪木古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabuki Kofun Cluster|qq=}} downstream, which predominantly feature [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]], the Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster is composed entirely of round Kofuns. Apart from the Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun and the second mound, which has a diameter of 29 meters, most of the mounds are smaller, measuring around 20 meters in diameter.

Although no excavation has been conducted, surveys indicate that the surrounding trench has a width of 5–9 meters. A surrounding embankment follows the outer edge of the trench, giving the mound a total length of approximately 85 meters, including the embankment. The lack of [[:en:Haniwa|haniwa]] and the mound's construction in the [[:en:7th century|7th century]] have been noted. However, the difference in type compared to the nearby {{ill|Danotsuka Kofun|ja|段ノ塚古墳|1=Dannozuka Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Danotsuka Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Dannozuka Kofun|qq=}} along the Sakutagawa River, which was also built in the 7th century as a square Kofun, remains a topic for further study.

