In contrast to nearby kofun clusters, such as the {{ill|Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|小池大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}} and the [[:en:Shibayama Kofun Cluster|Shibayama Kofun Cluster]] upstream on the eastern bank, or the {{ill|Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|ja|大堤権現塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kabuki Kofun Cluster|ja|蕪木古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabuki Kofun Cluster|qq=}} downstream, which predominantly feature [[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]], the Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster is composed entirely of round Kofuns. Apart from the Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun and the second mound, which has a diameter of 29 meters, most of the mounds are smaller, measuring around 20 meters in diameter.

Although no excavation has been conducted, surveys indicate that the surrounding trench has a width of 5–9 meters. A surrounding embankment follows the outer edge of the trench, giving the mound a total length of approximately 85 meters, including the embankment. The lack of [[:en:Haniwa|haniwa]] and the mound's construction in the [[:en:7th century|7th century]] have been noted. However, the difference in type compared to the nearby {{ill|Danotsuka Kofun|ja|段ノ塚古墳|1=Dannozuka Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Danotsuka Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Dannozuka Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} along the Sakutagawa River, which was also built in the 7th century as a square Kofun, remains a topic for further study.

