In contrast to nearby kofun clusters, such as the {{ill|Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Otsuka Kofun|lt=Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|小池大塚古墳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koike Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}} and the {{ill|Shibayama Kofun Cluster|en|Shibayama Kofun Cluster|WD=Q11614635|lt=Shibayama Kofun Cluster|1=Shibayama Kofun Cluster}} upstream on the eastern bank, or the {{ill|Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōtsutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|lt=Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|ja|大堤権現塚古墳|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōzutsumi Gongenzuka Kofun|qq=}} and {{ill|Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kaburagi Kofun Group|lt=Kabuki Kofun Cluster|ja|蕪木古墳群|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kabuki Kofun Cluster|qq=}} downstream, which predominantly feature {{ill|Zenpō-kōen-fun|en|Zenpō-kōen-fun|WD=Q11268718|lt=Zenpō-kōen-fun|1=Zenpō-kōen-fun}}, the Ōtsuka Kofun Cluster is composed entirely of round Kofuns. Apart from the Yamamuro Himezuka Kofun and the second mound, which has a diameter of 29 meters, most of the mounds are smaller, measuring around 20 meters in diameter.

